<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-09-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Viral Infections</TITLE><BODY>CMV can cause symptoms from almost any organ as well as unspecific symptoms such as fever, malaise, and bone marrow suppression in stem cell transplant patients. However, the most important clinical entities in allo-HSCT patients are pneumonia, gastroenteritis, and retinitis.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>